# PR Message Rules

## Output Format (MANDATORY)
- All PR messages MUST be written in Markdown
- Must include these sections:
    - Title
    - Description
    - Changes

## Title Rules
- Must be clear, short, and descriptive
- Prefer Conventional Commits format:
    - feat
    - fix
    - refactor
    - style
    - docs
    - chore
- Format:
    - `<type>: <short description>`
- If the project does not use Conventional Commits:
    - Use a clean, descriptive title without prefix


## Changes Section Rules
- Must always be included
- Must use bullet points only
- One change per line
- Must reflect only real changes from git history

## Quality Rules
- DO NOT invent or assume changes
- DO NOT include raw code in PR messages
- DO NOT use vague wording (e.g. "improved things", "fixed issues")
- All descriptions must be specific and reviewable


## Markdown Rules
- Must use proper Markdown formatting:
    - `##` headings
    - bullet points (`-`)
    - clean spacing between sections
- Output must be directly usable in GitHub


## Validation Rules
- Before output, ensure: 
    - All required sections exist
    - No invented or missing changes
    - Consistent formatting
    - Compliance with project commit style